      "correctAnswer": "C",
      "explanation": "Maximum bit rate = 2B \u00d7 log\u2082M = 2 \u00d7 20000 \u00d7 log\u2082(2) = 40000 \u00d7 1 = 40000 bps = 40 kbps.",
      "difficulty": "medium"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-9",
      "question": "What happens to signal strength as it travels through a medium?",
